By Omololu Ogunmade President Muhammadu Buhari Friday in Abuja felicitated with notable journalist and publisher, Dele Momodu, on his 60th birthday. A statement by the president’s media adviser, Mr. Femi Adesina, said the president congratulated Momodu on his attainment of this milestone in good health and sound mind. He also said the president wished Momodu greater contributions to further emancipation of Nigeria in the years and decades to come. According to the statement, Buhari rejoiced with the family, friends and professional colleagues of the publisher of Ovation International, noting that he had left his indelible footprints in the annals of journalism in the country. “He wishes Momodu greater profundity of thoughts as he engages with readers of his weekly column, PENdulum,” the statement added.